t: Judge*p me, O Lord;*s for I have walked in mine integrity: I have trusted also in the Lord;*s therefore I shall not slide.
Examine*p me, O Lord,*s and prove me; try my reins and my heart.
For*p thy lovingkindness is before mine eyes: and I have walked in thy truth.
I*p have not sat with vain persons, neither will I go in with dissemblers.
I*p have hated the congregation of evil doers; and will not sit with the wicked.
I*p will wash mine hands in innocency: so will I compass thine altar, O Lord:*s
That*p I may publish with the voice of thanksgiving, and tell of all thy wondrous works.
Lord,*sp I have loved the habitation of thy house, and the place where thine honour dwelleth.
Gather*p not my soul with sinners, nor my life with bloody men:
In*p whose hands is mischief, and their right hand is full of bribes.
But*p as for me, I will walk in mine integrity: redeem me, and be merciful unto me.
My*p foot standeth in an even place: in the congregations will I bless the Lord.*s
